article.headline: Mississippi 53, Nicholls St. 41
article.story: OXFORD, Miss. -- David Huertas scored 14 points to lead Mississippi to a 53-41 victory over Nicholls State on Saturday. The Rebels (9-5), who trailed 28-25 early in the second half, dominated the final 15 minutes with scoring runs of 13-2 and 12-2 to pull away. Ole Miss shot 50 percent from the field (19 of 38). Huertas and Murphy Holloway, who each scored 10 points, combined to go 8 of 12 from the field. Ryan Bathie and Anatoly Bose scored 10 points each for the Colonels (6-6). Nicholls State, relying heavily on the perimeter shot, was only 5 of 26 from 3-point range and shot 31 percent from the field (15 of 49). Ole Miss led 25-22 at halftime. Nicholls State took its only lead at 28-25 on Fred Hunter's consecutive baskets with 17:40 left. The Rebels answered with a 13-2 run, building a 38-30 lead with 6:53 left.
